      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CABOVER CARL (1) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Temora over 457m behind Havoc One (26.77) in a Mix. Placed at his previous run. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Looks the one to beat on his best form. MAKING GEMS (5) boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 1.5 lengths (18.55) behind Got A Note at this track. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Expected to be in this for a long way. BUZZ LIGHTNING (2) is still a maiden after eight runs but rarely far away, the latest finishing out of the placings when fourth at Richmond Straight. Must be included in calculations. WHISKEY GRACE (6) is a Ike Mccorkindale-trained newcomer by Tommy Shelby out of Newhaven Nellie. Profiles nicely and can feature in the finish.",
